      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Standard benchmark problems (patch test, cantilever beam under end load) were executed and results compared to analytical solutions. Errors were within 0.5% for all benchmark cases. Required level set at Gradation 2 for medium model risk context."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A mesh convergence study must demonstrate that QoI values (stiffness, yield force) change by less than 2% between successive mesh refinements. Gradation 2 minimum required for medium model risk level.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted across three mesh densities (coarse: ~18k elements, medium: ~52k elements, fine: ~140k elements). Stiffness QoI varied by 1.3% between medium and fine meshes; yield force varied by 0.9%. The fine mesh was adopted for all production runs. Achieved Gradation 3 due to Richardson extrapolation also being applied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence criteria were set to residual tolerance of 1e-6. Nonlinear contact iterations converged within 50 substeps for all 11 model instances. No divergence events were recorded."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Simulation inputs were reviewed by a second analyst independent of the primary modeler. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were confirmed against the study protocol. No use errors were identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The chosen continuum mechanics model form (linear elastic titanium alloy with nonlinear contact) must be justified by published material characterization data and prior validation studies for metallic implant constructs. Gradation 3 required because model form assumptions directly govern all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties were sourced from ASTM F136 and confirmed against manufacturer certificates of conformance. Linear elastic assumption is appropriate below yield; nonlinear geometric effects captured via large-deformation formulation. Model form consistent with FDA guidance document on FEA of orthopedic implants."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Material properties, geometry dimensions, and boundary condition magnitudes were all sourced from traceable measurement records. Dimensional measurements of the physical constructs were used to parameterize the CAD geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 physical constructs must be tested, sourced from at least two independent laboratories, with sample-to-sample variability characterized via coefficient of variation reported for each QoI. Gradation 3 required to support statistical comparison against model predictions.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested: six at Laboratory A and five at Laboratory B. Coefficient of variation for stiffness was 4.2%, for yield force 5.8%, and for force at 40 mm 3.9%. Inter-laboratory variability was within measurement uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single loading rate (5 mm/min) and a single angular offset per ASTM F1717 protocol. Only static compression-bending was evaluated; fatigue and dynamic conditions were not covered. This limits generalizability but is appropriate for the stated COU. Achieved Gradation 2 due to single test condition; required Gradation 3 not met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Model boundary conditions were mapped directly to the experimental fixture geometry. Applied displacement and support constraints in the FEA replicate the ASTM F1717 test fixture configuration as confirmed by overlay comparison of fixture drawings and model geometry."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model predictions must fall within 10% of the experimental mean for each QoI, and the validation metric E/uval must be less than 1.96 for all three QoIs. Gradation 3 required given that output comparison is the primary evidence of model credibility for this COU.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: FEA predicted 312 N/mm vs. experimental mean 308 N/mm (1.3% difference, E/uval=0.41). Yield force: FEA 1,847 N vs. experimental mean 1,891 N (2.3% difference, E/uval=0.78). Force at 40 mm: FEA 2,204 N vs. experimental mean 2,251 N (2.1% difference, E/uval=0.62). All three QoIs satisfy the acceptance bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
